 ('537', '573', 'en_us', 'Greg Proulx', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Partner', 'greg.proulx@bridgepartnersconsulting.com', 'Greg is a senior business executive with more than 25 years of experience growing direct revenue and partner-leveraged businesses at technology firms including HP, Oracle, and Microsoft. His cross-disciplinary experience benefits clients in partner and channel development, business strategy and planning, and field operations.\n\nAs General Manager of Microsoft\'s US Enterprise Partner business, Greg was responsible for a large managed partner ecosystem of over 500 global, regional, and local partners. He is highly effective communicating with execu-\ntives, collaborating across groups, driving influence without authority, and instilling trust in teams.\n\nA computer engineering graduate from UCLA, Greg relishes time spent with his family, enjoying the outdoors around Puget Sound or travelling around the world. Look for him training for triathlons or team challenges like the Nike Hood to Coast or the Ragnar Relay Series.', '/images/uploads/people/Greg-Proulx.jpg', '', 'Leadership', '[]', NULL, NULL, '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '7627eb7a-a0d8-4c01-ad67-6e0e33b57cac'),
 ('538', '574', 'en_us', 'Tania Fernandez de Castro', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Director', 'tania.f.decastro@bridgepartnersconsulting.com', 'Tania has worked in the technology, government, manufacturing, and education sectors for over 18 years. Her multi-industry experience and approach has been a key factor in her ability to clearly understand business challenges, priorities, and drivers to deliver well-thought-out business solutions for her clients.\n\nShe has built and managed programs in technical and non-technical marketing, sales experience, enablement for internal and external audience, training, and social/community engagement.\n\nAreas of Expertise:\n\n\n	Field and Partner Enablement Programs\n	Sales Excellence - Account Planning\n	Process Improvement and Optimization\n	Global Product Launch Programs\n	Project Management\n	Connected Sales and Marketing Programs\n	Product/Solution Marketing\n\n\nRecent Highlights:\n\n\n	Developed the SQL Server 2012 3-year Technical Readiness Strategy\n	Redesigned the entire operations and communication strategy for a global technology corporation\n	Developed and managed campaigns of local, state, and federal governments, including Gov. Gregoire 2010 Whistler Olympics Taskforce\n\n\nBorn and raised in Mexico, Tania holds a Political Science degree from The Evergreen State College. She is fluent in Spanish and also speaks conversational Portuguese.', '/images/uploads/people/Tania-Fernandez-de-Castro.jpg', '', 'Leadership', '[]', NULL, NULL, '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', 'ecacbe7c-b15e-4f01-b8d9-efdb11f86773'),
 ('539', '575', 'en_us', 'Ezra Fain', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Director', 'ezra.fain@bridgepartnersconsulting.com', 'Ezra\'s experience spans multiple industries including technology, communi-\ncations, financial services, aerospace, and consumer packaged goods with firms such as Microsoft, T-Mobile, and Boeing. He is intrisically motivated to work on projects that change the way people think about their business and the work they do.\n\nEzra has a deep set of skills and experience in building programs to enable a “Compete” muscle across an enterprise. He understands how market forces and\nbusiness models can work for or against an enterprise and brings a keen sense of how internal structures can drive competitive success. Ezra has a background in strategy, marketing, operations, finance, and process engineering.\n\nEzra’s loves boating, fishing and travel.', '/images/uploads/people/Ezra-Fain.jpg', 'Five Keys to Building a Compete Culture', 'Leadership', '[]', NULL, NULL, '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '9427ce13-df3e-4987-bb2e-9352dad2fd08'),
 ('540', '576', 'en_us', 'Blair J. Foerster', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Managing Consultant', 'blair.foerster@bridgepartnersconsulting.com', 'Blair is a seasoned project manager with a track record of successful engagements in online advertising, human resources, and competitive strategy. Prior to his consulting career, he worked for a Fortune 500 service bureau as account manager in business-to-business sales, where he specialized in cultivating relationships with CPA firms.\n\nHe is passionate about sales, marketing, and business strategy. Being tested with a steep learning curve and attaining confidence in new subject matter excites and motivates Blair for each new day. He holds a BA in Business Administration from the University of San Diego and earned an MBA from Seattle University.\n\nIn his free time, Blair loves outdoor activities such as fishing, hunting, skiing, and hiking. He also enjoys traveling with his wife Sarah and experiencing diverse cultures in countries around the globe.', '/images/uploads/people/Blair-Foerster.jpg', '', 'Consultant', '[]', NULL, NULL, '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2dac9ff0-783e-471d-b2b2-4b6a5555af18'),
 ('541', '577', 'en_us', 'Chase Morgan', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Partner', 'chase.morgan@bridgepartnersconsulting.com', 'Whether your sales strategy needs retooling or you want to expand and extend your partner alliances, Chase has the breadth of vision to make it happen. With more than 20 years of success building strategies and driving complex sales for organizations such as Microsoft, Siebel Systems, and IBM, Chase’s focus is on profitable sales excellence and world-class teams. Her smart, outside-the-box approach yields big results.\n\nChase polished her general management skills at Harvard Business School and holds an undergraduate degree from the University of the South.\n\nWhen she’s not working with clients, Chase can be found serving on the Board of Directors for the Alliance for Education, planning her next Seafair party, hiking and practicing yoga, or brushing up on her Spanish for another trip to Mexico.', '/images/uploads/people/Chase-Morgan-v2.jpg', 'Help! Why Aren’t We Winning in the Cloud?', 'Leadership', '[]', NULL, NULL, '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', 'd8c18ebc-821a-4dc1-a606-76dd1ee9c0de'),
 ('542', '578', 'en_us', 'Rebecca Jones', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Partner', 'rebecca.jones@bridgepartnersconsulting.com', 'Rebecca is a business manager and Partner who knows how to reach and engage customers. She has two decades of experience working with organizations like AT&amp;T Wireless, T-Mobile, Microsoft, and Seattle Children’s Hospital.   She partners with leadership in marketing and sales to define campaign and go-to-market strategy, build repeatable frameworks, and implement results-driven marketing programs.\n \nRebecca has led teams on the agency and company side and has deep industry expertise in technology and mobile. Rebecca is passionate about the art of developing meaningful customer stories, driving results through a lean-process approach to marketing, and helping clients transform their marketing organizations and deliver sustainable growth through digital and marketing automation.  \n \nRebecca resides in Seattle, Washington and holds a BA in Fine Arts and English Literature from Lake Forest College.  When she\'s not at work, Rebecca spends time with family and friends, chasing adventure with her husband and two sons, and enjoying the perfect glass of wine.', '/images/uploads/people/Rebecca-Jones.jpg', 'How Marketing Leaders are Moving to the CloudFraming a Conversation', 'Leadership', '[]', NULL, NULL, '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '81735656-e903-446c-8b05-0fadae187f5e'),
 ('543', '579', 'en_us', 'Patty Vu', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Senior Consultant', 'patty.vu@bridgepartnersconsulting.com', 'Patty brings to the table solid experience in process optimization and execution plus developing skills in marketing and project management. She is recognized for her critical thinking and attention to detail, as well as for keeping even keel, full steam ahead under tight deadlines and high pressure. Patty thrives on stepping into a project with multiple work streams, dependencies, stakeholders, and cross-functional teams to optimize work and collaboration.\n\nPatty holds a double degree in business administration and economics from the University of Washington, with concentrations in marketing and finance.\n\nIn her free time, she enjoys the company of her family and friends. Animal rescue also ranks high on her list.', '/images/uploads/people/Patty-Vu.jpg', '', 'Consultant', '[]', NULL, NULL, '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2f04e3ca-96ff-44b2-b6d8-fb80f59fbf91'),
 ('544', '580', 'en_us', 'John Tribble', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Director', 'john.tribble@bridgepartnersconsulting.com', '<p>John loves analytical projects such as ROI modeling and problem solving. He excels in bringing consensus across multiple groups, especially in situations that require diplomacy. He is energized by the treasure hunt aspect of consulting. John strives to blaze new trails and to learn or achieve something new. Reaching goals and exceeding clients’ expectations fuel John’s engine.</p>\n\n<p>Known for his creativity, John is adept at identifying time and resource efficiencies to make teams more effective. He’s even brought lessons learned coaching youth sports into business team settings.</p>\n\n<p>John’s into soccer, golf, and triathlons. His kids make him laugh on a daily basis.</p>', '/images/uploads/people/John-Tribble-2.jpg', 'Perspectives from the Pitch: Building Strong TeamsFour Coaching Pitfalls to AvoidHow to Tell Your Boss He is Wrong', 'Leadership', '[\"leadership\"]', NULL, NULL, '2016-08-15 23:37:52', '2016-08-19 17:46:32', '3c0b4011-1909-4e24-beb1-de0d14bd2e52'),
 ('545', '581', 'en_us', 'Abby Rzegocki', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Senior Consultant', 'abby.rzegocki@bridgepartnersconsulting.com', '<p>Abby Rzegocki is a project management specialist with a passion for technology. Adept at wrangling details and driving to execution, her work<br />is enhanced by her strong teaming and communication skills. Abby has a background in sales excellence, business management and operations.</p>\n\n<p>Abby holds a BA in Political Science from the University of Washington. She<br />has additional certifications from UW in Administration Management and is a certified Microsoft Office Specialist.</p>\n\n<p>A Washington state native, Abby is married and has two children. She has “followed the snow” between Lake Tahoe and New Zealand and enjoys the outdoors at every possible opportunity.</p>', '/images/uploads/people/Abby-Rzegocki.jpg', '', 'Consultant', '[\"consultant\"]', NULL, NULL, '2016-08-15 23:37:52', '2016-08-19 18:31:04', '95762fb2-aa91-4182-b422-e1aff52972ef'),
 ('546', '582', 'en_us', 'Overview', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, NULL, '2016-08-18 17:52:21', '2016-08-18 18:50:25', '11cf77d5-49ec-4313-80e5-ac48275a46f9'),
 ('547', '583', 'en_us', 'Digital', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', 'Technological disruptions, changing industry structures, and evolving customer behavior…Don Draper couldn’t have pictured this. ', '<p>The digital-enabled customer has turned the business world upside down. Marketing leaders worldwide wrestle with how to build mutually beneficial relationships with customers that have more options, more information, and more opinions than ever before.</p>\n\n<p>Channel models are more complex, speed-to-market pressures are more intense, business agility is at a premium, and the tools and techniques for connecting with customers are creating new challenges each day.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>But with these changes comes opportunity, and making the most of this opportunity and the possibilities presented by the convergence of digital’s “big four”—cloud, mobile, social, and big data—requires a comprehensive understanding of digital platforms and their capabilities.</p>', '2016-08-18 17:52:33', '2016-08-19 18:31:19', '1adec7ae-0799-494e-9c41-cf58c5b673a9'),
 ('548', '584', 'en_us', 'Digital GTM Strategy', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', 'Digital GTM Strategy', '<p>Without a vision on how digital platforms, tools, and capabilities fit into your GTM strategy, business opportunity can pass you by. We can help you craft a digitally-savvy and customer-focused business model powered by modern techniques and solid digital fundamentals.</p>', '2016-08-18 17:53:24', '2016-08-19 00:22:54', '51a7e8b9-23b2-4a5f-9ae7-bf8bd381e0e6'),
