 ('215', '506', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jim Schwalbe\",\"slug\":\"jim-schwalbe\",\"postDate\":1471304260,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Jim is a results-driven consulting executive bringing leadership and discipline required to get\\/keep large transformational programs on the right track.\\u00a0 With over 25 years of experience and a long list of Fortune 500 successes, he has a unique ability to help synchronize PMO\\u2019s, steering committees and boards to monitor the right KPI\\u2019s and get to the \\u201ctruth\\u201d.\\u00a0 He drives deliberate intensity on eliminating hurdles to success and focusing on achieving real measurable value.\\n\\nPrior to joining Bridge Partners, Jim was Vice President and Market Leader for North Highland and spent the rest of his years split between Deloitte and Andersen Consulting (Accenture). \\u00a0He has system implementation certifications in Oracle, SAP, JDE and also has a manufacturing planning and inventory control certification (APICS CPIM). \\u00a0Jim earned a Bachelor of Science degree with honors from Milwaukee School of Engineering in Computer Science & Engineering.\\n\\nOutside of work, you will see Jim coaching or watching his boys in soccer or football and his girls in competitive cheerleading.\\u00a0 He also enjoys big game hunting, fishing, family cruises, beaches and just about anything outdoors.\\u00a0\",\"83\":\"jim.schwalbe@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Jim_Schwalbe_1.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Regional Managing Director\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:41', '2016-08-15 23:37:41', '7d575896-0720-4c0c-ac78-2d425066cfb6'),
 ('216', '507', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Ethan Kalkwarf\",\"slug\":\"ethan-kalkwarf\",\"postDate\":1471304261,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Ethan brings years of experience in digital marketing and brand development. He works to create a clear and consistent Bridge Partners brand across all channels. He collaborates with leadership from across the firm to drive content marketing, communications, and sales enablement.\\n\\nHe also serves on the Chairman\\u2019s Advisory Board at Cinemark Theaters, advising the chairman of the board on strategic marketing opportunities. Passionate about eradicating cancer during our lifetime, Ethan previously served as the nation\\u2019s youngest event chair for a Relay For Life event, increasing YOY revenue 32% and placing in the top 4% of high-growth events.\\n\\nOutside of the office, Ethan stays busy with family and friends. In his spare time, you\\u2019ll find him with a volunteering with Young Life or reading a good book. Ethan graduated from Liberty University with a BS in Marketing and Economics.\",\"83\":\"ethan.kalkwarf@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Ethan-Kalkwarf.jpg\",\"86\":\"Five Content Marketing Mistakes to Avoid\",\"82\":\"Marketing Coordinator\",\"87\":\"Corporate Staff\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:41', '2016-08-15 23:37:41', 'dc75f0d4-7ee1-4b99-a95a-fa7c75ee2a95'),
 ('217', '508', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Tarsi Hall\",\"slug\":\"tarsi-hall\",\"postDate\":1471304261,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Tarsi has over a decade of experience in developing marketing strategies for emerging and iconic companies. She has led teams through strategic planning, branding, and change management efforts and has consistently surpassed expectations. Tarsi\\u2019s strength is helping clients identify root causes that hamstring success; spotting opportunities that are not being maximized; and recognizing clients\\u2019 unique purpose to differentiate them within the market. She excels at mindfully connecting vision and purpose through content marketing and tracking growth through data analysis.\\n\\n\\nShe has successfully developed strategies for Microsoft, Avanade, Pfizer, MD Anderson, City University of Seattle, DigiPen Institute of Technology and others. Throughout her work, she has delivered high-impact results that have shifted internal and external perceptions and, increased engagement and sales overall.\\n\\n\\nTarsi holds a Master of Arts degree from The George Washington University in Political Management and lives in Seattle. If you see her around town, she is probably on her yoga mat, a standup paddle board, or at the market buying something fun to cook for her husband and beagle.\",\"83\":\"tarsi.hall@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Tarsi_Hall.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:41', '2016-08-15 23:37:41', '32b4b92d-9788-4062-ad9f-bd18a0805b55'),
