 ('220', '511', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Scott Smith\",\"slug\":\"scott-smith\",\"postDate\":1471304261,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Scott is a senior professional services executive focused on large global enterprises. He possesses a BSBA in Economics and a Master of Science in Industrial Management. Scott has spent 28 years dedicated to large-scale corporate strategy, information technology and business process transformation work extending to a diverse range of global enterprises, industries, and geographies.\\n\\nScott has substantial experience with large scale enterprises. He has managed a Public Sector consulting practice for Unisys Corporation and has built a successful systems integration consulting firm. He guided his firm through a merger and then participated in a successful public offering on NASDAQ for the combined legal entity.\\n\\nAreas of Expertise:\\n\\n\\n\\tIT Strategy & Transformation\\n\\tEnterprise Information Technology\\n\\tBack-Office Process Transformation\\n\\tMergers & Acquisitions Integration\\n\\tEnterprise Business Systems\\n\\tBenchmarking & Organizational Redesign\\n\\n\\nWhen not working with clients, Scott serves on the Boards of several non-profits focused on child advocacy, homelessness, and families of cancer victims. Scott is a long time golf enthusiast, runner, and active in his local community.\",\"83\":\"scott.smith@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Scott-Smith.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Director\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:41', '2016-08-15 23:37:41', '0edd4147-39f0-442d-96ee-d998f6861079'),
 ('221', '512', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Vikrant Khosla\",\"slug\":\"vikrant-khosla\",\"postDate\":1471304261,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Vikrant is a highly seasoned management consultant and business leader with 20 years of experience at some of the most influential multi-national corporations. He has strong aptitude and a proven track record of delivering innovative and impactful results based on understanding each organization\\u2019s unique business challenges, creating highly trusted and collaborative partnerships, and designing solutions that maximize top- and bottom-line measures of success.\\n\\nVikrant\\u2019s expertise includes organizational strategy and design, operational planning and execution, business process transformation, program management, change management, content management, analytics, user experience design, technology solutions for cloud \\/ mobile \\/ web and on \\/ off \\/ near shore IT managed services. His industry experience includes software, consumer products, aerospace & defense, communications and media.\\n\\nPrior to joining Bridge Partners, Vikrant was Vice President of Consulting Services at Hitachi Consulting.\\u00a0 He has a Bachelor\\u2019s in Mechanical Engineering (Bangalore, India), attended graduate school to study Aerospace Engineering (University of Cincinnati, OH) and received his MBA from Foster School of Business (University of Washington, WA).\",\"83\":\"vikrant.khosla@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Vikrant_Khosla.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Director\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:41', '2016-08-15 23:37:41', '7f92a80e-b8f1-45fb-a8cd-e1f5647f97a0'),
 ('222', '513', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"D\\u2019Laina Boynton\",\"slug\":\"dlaina-boynton\",\"postDate\":1471304262,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"D\\u2019Laina is a results-driven marketer with more than ten years of experience in consulting and project management. Her areas of expertise include digital and social marketing, from campaign and content development to community management. She helps organizations build digital media plans to position their products and build robust online communities. You can also find her leading training workshops to help others increase sales through social selling.\\n\\nIn addition to receiving a BA in Sociology from Western Washington University, D\\u2019Laina has earned a number of marketing certificates from the University of Washington and General Assembly. She is currently a candidate for the Technology Management MBA from the University of Washington.\\n\\nIn her spare time, D\\u2019Laina loves to challenge herself by running marathons and traveling the world, having visited 27 countries and counting. She has a passion for serving the local community and leads the Bridge Partners Volunteer Community.\",\"83\":\"dlaina.boynton@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/DLaina-Boynton.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Consultant\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:42', '2016-08-15 23:37:42', 'd4a67885-5fdd-421c-9268-1f765a229b37'),
 ('223', '514', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Amy Lau\",\"slug\":\"amy-lau\",\"postDate\":1471304262,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Amy brings over 20 years of enterprise sales and consulting experience with global clients like LinkedIn, Raytheon, and Allianz Global. She has orchestrated complex solution sales within technology, cloud, financial services, legal, and social media sectors. Amy loves applying her relationship building skills and analytical business acumen to develop strategic, purposeful partnerships with her clients as a trusted advisor. She enjoys collaborating with customers to develop strategies and roadmaps to achieve their goals. At Bridge, she works with teams to drive insight and actionable advice to influence the direction of an organization.\\n\\nWith a diverse background, Amy was born in China and has lived in Hong Kong before emigrating to the U.S. She has a BA in Business Administration and a Literary Fiction Certificate from the University of Washington. She speaks two dialects of Chinese, is conversant in French, and is learning Spanish and Italian. When she\\u2019s not working, she\\u2019s either finishing her fiction novel or enjoying leisure time with friends and family.\",\"83\":\"amy.lau@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Amy-Lau.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Consultant\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:42', '2016-08-15 23:37:42', 'fd55a3d3-2182-4081-b982-09d7eb01641a'),
 ('224', '515', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Crystal Guthrie\",\"slug\":\"crystal-guthrie\",\"postDate\":1471304262,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Crystal is an innovative marketing leader with 20 years of experience in data-driven marketing and business management. She has lead digital and product marketing efforts for organizations including Microsoft, GE Capital, Merrill Lynch, CNBC, and Fidelity. Crystal builds relationships with leadership in marketing, sales, engineering, finance, and operations to achieve positive business results in start-up, M&A, and rebranding situations.\\n\\nAreas of Expertise and Focus:\\n\\n\\n\\tProduct and Solution Marketing\\n\\tMessaging and Positioning\\n\\tCustomer Segmentation and Business Intelligence\\n\\tConnected Sales and Marketing Programs\\n\\tGlobal Launch Programs and Management\\n\\n\\nCrystal holds an M.A. in Economics from Fordham University and a Certificate in Marketing from Kellogg School of Management at Northwestern University. She completed undergraduate studies at Texas Tech University.\\n\\nWhen she\\u2019s not working with clients, Crystal passes her time cooking meals for her family and friends, catching a live music show, or skiing\\/trail running in the mountains.\",\"83\":\"crystal.guthrie@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Crystal-Guthrie.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Managing Consultant\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:42', '2016-08-15 23:37:42', '598ed2ef-7924-492f-a4b0-b67075f39409'),
 ('225', '516', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Christopher Ferris\",\"slug\":\"christopher-ferris\",\"postDate\":1471304262,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Chris has over 20 years of experience delivering marketing systems solutions across a broad spectrum of industries. Working for companies like Microsoft, AT&T, Netflix, and T-Mobile, Chris has a strong record of creating elegant solutions for complex business challenges. He is a Six Sigma black belt with decades of experience with logical design, digital asset management, global content workflow design, and business and strategic analysis.\\n\\nChris is currently working with Microsoft\\u2019s Small and Medium Business group to create and establish a marketing automation program to support 36 countries around the world.\\n\\nAREAS OF EXPERTISE:\\n\\n\\n\\tGlobal System and Process Architecture\\n\\tMarketing Automation Discovery and Implementation\\n\\tSix Sigma Planning and Efficiency\\n\\tGlobal Program Management\\n\\n\\nOutside of the office, Chris is always seeking a new adventure. He is an accomplished musician, avid runner, and high performance driving enthusiast.\",\"83\":\"christopher.ferris@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Chrisopher-Ferris.jpg\",\"86\":\"Getting Up and Running with Marketing Automation\",\"82\":\"Senior Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:42', '2016-08-15 23:37:42', 'bc2f381d-fce7-4aac-a52b-a4bf24c0b543'),
 ('226', '517', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Isak Lopez\",\"slug\":\"isak-lopez\",\"postDate\":1471304262,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Isak brings a wide breadth of experience in the business operations and hospitality realms to Bridge Partners. With roles at Royal Caribbean International, Celebrity Cruises and Holland America Line, his skill sets run the gamut of client and corporate services, from customer operations to revenue management. He has a deep appreciation for his role in developing the employee culture at Bridge Partners, a key asset of our organization. He holds a BA from Florida Atlantic University which includes a double major in Management and Marketing.\\n\\nA native of Miami, Florida, Isak is now very proud to call Seattle home. He relishes opportunities to explore the Pacific Northwest, with trail hikes in the Cascade Range or weekend escapes to the forests and shorelines of Olympic National Park. He enjoys attending performances that range from the theatre to film festivals and is grateful for Seattle\\u2019s fondness with all things sci-fi. He is very proud to participate in Seattle\\u2019s vibrant cultural scene as a singing member of the Seattle Men\\u2019s Chorus.\",\"83\":\"isak.lopez@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Isak-Lopez.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Business Manager\",\"87\":\"Corporate Staff\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:42', '2016-08-15 23:37:42', 'f702dac6-352d-4891-a807-af185d1c46e1'),
 ('227', '518', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Rachel Evans\",\"slug\":\"rachel-evans\",\"postDate\":1471304262,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Rachel is a human resources professional with an extensive background in benefits administration, policies, and compliance. As the Senior Human Resource Specialist, she oversees the pre-employment process, benefits administration, and all reporting and compliance. Rachel has nearly a decade of experience helping companies build better work environments.\\n\\nRachel is solution oriented and results-driven. Over the last eight years, Rachel has learned that what really matters in the workplace is connection, collaboration, and passion. She graduated from Central Washington University and holds a PHR certification from the Human Resources Certification Institute. When she\\u2019s not working, Rachel enjoys crocheting, cooking, and spending time in the backyard with her dog, Casper.\",\"83\":\"rachel.evans@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Rachel-Evans.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"HR Specialist and Benefits Manager\",\"87\":\"Corporate Staff\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:42', '2016-08-15 23:37:42', '925c445e-22dd-44d3-9ff4-c2be69877192'),
 ('228', '519', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Stevie Frink\",\"slug\":\"stevie-frink\",\"postDate\":1471304263,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Stevie is an experienced case management professional with a unique background in workers\\u2019 compensation and employer\\/employee relations. As an HR Coordinator, she is committed to maintaining a workplace that values communication, teamwork, and mutual respect.\\u00a0Her position allows her to ensure all employees feel valued and well-informed of what Bridge Partners has to offer.\\n\\nStevie was raised in Tacoma, Washington. \\u00a0She earned a\\u00a0Bachelor of Arts from the University of Washington and a Masters of Psychology from the University of the Rockies. Away from the office, Stevie enjoys football, reading, cooking, and spending time with her family.\",\"83\":\"stevie.frink@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Stevie-Fink.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"HR Coordinator\",\"87\":\"Corporate Staff\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', '8f5b6537-587f-45c9-a469-8952a2c88f78'),
 ('229', '520', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kate Macartney\",\"slug\":\"kate-macartney\",\"postDate\":1471304263,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Kate has experience in change management, talent management, and workforce effectiveness. Kate can fill the role of a strategic thinker, and a hands on builder. Her can-do attitude helps clients turn thoughts into action and create effective results.\\n\\nPart of Kate\\u2019s experience includes assisting organizations with change management strategies, including developing training tools, audience engagement methods, and communication design. She enjoys working hand in hand with the client to understand their organizational needs, design a tailored approach, and collaboratively implement their customized strategies.\\n\\nKate completed her undergraduate work at the University of Washington, earning a Bachelors in Business, focused on Business Communication and Marketing. She earned her Masters in Business Administration at Seattle University and a Certificate of Leadership Formation.\",\"83\":\"Kate.Macartney@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Kate-Macartney.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', 'b152bf52-0348-4d6f-aac2-099fc4830e10'),
 ('230', '521', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kelly Bateman\",\"slug\":\"kelly-bateman\",\"postDate\":1471304263,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Kelly comes to Bridge Partners with decades of experience in supporting business consulting practices. She began her career with Arthur Andersen and has since worked for several firms of varying sizes as a talent management expert, as well as a recruiter. She brings a broad skill set, including consultant performance management, bench management, career guidance, and project resourcing.\\n\\nAs the Director of Talent Management, Kelly works to develop the strengths of our consultants. She provides leadership around resourcing and staffing management, assists with the improvement of the performance management and training processes, and serves as an a advocate for our consultants. In her personal time, Kelly enjoys cheering for her son, Niles, on the basketball court, taking her dog, Leisl, to the dog-park, attending concerts, reading great books, and traveling.\",\"83\":\"kelly.bateman@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Kelly-Bateman.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Director of Talent Management\",\"87\":\"Leadership\\n  Corporate Staff\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', 'db64ed45-ab32-4988-911c-e1ec1f5bbac8'),
 ('231', '522', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Gordon Matlock\",\"slug\":\"gordon-matlock\",\"postDate\":1471304263,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Gordon is a big picture, strategic thinker who knows how to build strong, enduring cyber partnerships with clients. He has over fifteen years of leadership experience in the U.S. government, at a National Laboratory, and for a cybersecurity start-up company. Gordon has advised senior executives and developed relationships, teams, initiatives, and capabilities to enhance cybersecurity.\\n\\nGordon polished his policy and strategic thinking skills advising the U.S. Senate Select Committee on Intelligence. He has also been an advisor to a U.S. Senator, Congressman, and a Governor. As a business and technology leader, Gordon has directed policy and technology initiatives at Battelle\\/PNNL and led sales, business development, and marketing as an SVP for a cybersecurity start-up. Bottom-line, Gordon knows how to bridge the gap between the sometimes divergent technology and policy worlds.\\n\\nAfter earning a BA from the University of Idaho, Gordon went on to the United States Naval War College where he earned a Masters in National Security and Strategic Studies. When he\\u2019s not collaborating and forming cyber partnerships, you can find Gordon coaching football and soccer, or swimming, hiking, and skiing with his three kids.\",\"83\":\"gordon.matlock@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Gordon_Matlock.jpg\",\"86\":\"Cybersecurity GuideCybersecurity: Know the Enemy of Your Business\",\"82\":\"Cyber Practice Lead\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', '587f89c3-9db2-4b6b-bf20-049c8fde305c'),
 ('232', '523', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kyrsa Dixon\",\"slug\":\"kyrsa-dixon\",\"postDate\":1471304263,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"As an integrated marketing strategist, Kyrsa has spent 15 years helping organizations of all shapes and sizes tell their brand story to the people who matter most. This work has taken her around the world. From renowned wine country to urban hubs of technological innovation, Kyrsa brings a global perspective to her work.\\n\\nWhether managing an international PR program or developing a digital communications campaign or content marketing strategy, Kyrsa can quickly distill her clients\' marketing and messaging complexities into effective narratives and engagement plans. She enjoys combining the analytical with the creative to solve problems and drive tangible results. Whenever possible, Kyrsa loves to spend time playing outdoors, traveling the world, learning new things, and enjoying a good glass of wine.\",\"83\":\"kyrsa.dixon@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Kyrsa_Dixon.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', 'e050791c-7be7-4707-ad71-0d4a1acdbcb8'),
 ('233', '524', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Michael Iem\",\"slug\":\"michael-iem\",\"postDate\":1471304263,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Michael has over 25 years experience in product marketing and project management. Prior to joining Bridge Partners, he was the Director of Marketing at a startup called grandPad and spent years in leadership at Microsoft. After working on the launch of Visual Studio.Net and Windows Server 2003, Michael founded a consulting company, The Ziem Group Inc. He later joined Riverbed Technology as a Senior Product Marketing Manager focusing on application architectures via advanced load balancing and web content optimization.\\n\\nMichael holds a BS in Industrial Engineering from Purdue University. He spent his college summers working at NASA, where he helped design the International Space Station and directed a large team of students to put experiments on the Space Shuttle. Outside of the office, his passion for photography and mountaineering has taken him from the summit of Mt. Rainier to the mountains of Patagonia in South America.\",\"83\":\"michael.iem@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Michael-Iem.jpeg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', '1fdc291b-5ae6-4af8-bf3b-94cfcc241ca1'),
 ('234', '525', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Curtis Metz\",\"slug\":\"curtis-metz\",\"postDate\":1471304263,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Curtis is a global business and technology professional with 20 years of experience in project and program management, marketing, digital marketing and web analytics, and startups. He loves to learn and is willing to take on any task where needed most. He thrives on wearing many hats.\\n\\nIn all his projects, programs and products, Curtis likes to start with the customer. He has a passion for understanding them, their business, their needs, and their pain points. He then leverages that knowledge into a strategy, execution plans, and finally the delivery of that service or product. This passion was born out of his fierce interest in business and business models as well has his deep desire to make a difference in people\\u2019s lives.\\n\\nHis past clients and employers include large public enterprises, most currently Microsoft, as well as nonprofits, retail, and various startups.\\n\\nCurtis holds an MBA focused on International Management from Thunderbird School of Global Management, and a BA in International Relations from San Francisco State University. He loves to travel, learn, teach, and to make life an adventure for him and his family.\",\"83\":\"curtis.metz@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Curtis-Metz.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', 'fc9d1629-b205-402c-b6a8-063ad8f95877'),
 ('235', '526', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"David Cunningham\",\"slug\":\"david-cunningham\",\"postDate\":1471304263,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"David comes to Bridge Partners with over 20 years of marketing, marketing automation, and communications experience in the high tech industry. He has spent the last 13 years within Microsoft and has developed a strong ability to work across organizations and facilitate detailed project management programs.\\n\\nOutside of the office, David loves to travel and explore new and exciting places. He can often be found in NAPA \\/ Sonoma or even Europe. He enjoys mountain or road biking, dining with friends and family, and experiencing new cultures.\",\"83\":\"david.cunningham@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/David-Cunningham.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', '2016-08-15 23:37:43', '0168dc92-8166-4afe-a3a6-7f074e908834'),
 ('236', '527', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Cynthia LaRowe\",\"slug\":\"cynthia-larowe\",\"postDate\":1471304264,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Cynthia is a senior leader who specializes in defining and implementing people and change strategies that set companies apart and radically improve their results. She has more than 25 years of experience leading global businesses at Microsoft and Starbucks and complex consulting projects at companies across multiple industries and functions.\\u00a0\\n\\nCynthia\\u2019s \\u201cin the trenches\\u201d experience managing start-up, mature, and turn-around organizations gives her an intimate understanding of the challenges businesses face. Her depth of knowledge in people strategy, organizational transformation, and how the modern workplace \\u201cworks\\u201d gives her a unique toolkit to address them. Cynthia balances a passion for innovation with a drive for simplicity, practicality, and results.\\u00a0\\n\\nAreas of Expertise:\\n\\n\\n\\tPeople strategy\\n\\tStrategy and leadership alignment\\n\\tOrganization, culture, and work design\\n\\tTalent strategy and management\\n\\tChange management\\n\\n\\nCynthia majored in English at Westmont College. She revels in exploring the world with her daughter, supporting arts and humanitarian organizations, and sharpening her edge as a fine art photographer.\\u00a0\",\"83\":\"cynthia.larowe@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Cynthia_LaRowe.jpg\",\"86\":\"From Hierarchy to Wirearchy \\u2013 Managing People & Change in the Digital WorldDispelling the Big Data Myth: A Practical Take on Talent Analytics\",\"82\":\"People and Change Practice Lead\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:44', '2016-08-15 23:37:44', '3bdecdb6-e3bb-42f5-b853-495358e12f8e'),
 ('237', '528', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jeff Kimbell\",\"slug\":\"jeff-kimbell\",\"postDate\":1471304264,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"For the past 25 years, Jeff has held various consulting and internal leadership roles, helping companies improve operations, develop new programs, and manage projects. He has successfully launched new GRC initiatives and partnered with business owners to understand and improve their security and privacy. Jeff has also assisted a diverse portfolio of companies in their manufacturing, distribution, logistics, and supply chain management.\\n\\nJeff is a graduate of the University of Washington\\u2019s Executive Development Program and also received his Bachelor of Science in Industrial Engineering from the UW. He is certified in Enterprise Risk Management and Six Sigma. As a licensed Industrial Professional Engineer, Jeff has extensive experience with Lean project management.\\n\\nOutside of the office, Jeff enjoys challenging hikes and epic bike rides, mentoring students through his church\\u2019s youth group, and spending time with his family. He also serves as the Vice Chair of the Executive Advisory Board for the UW\\u2019s Industrial and Systems Engineering Department.\",\"83\":\"jeff.kimbell@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Jeff-Kimbell.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:44', '2016-08-15 23:37:44', '318d2e96-dd5c-440d-81ca-2098dcace553'),
 ('238', '529', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Frank Myers\",\"slug\":\"frank-myers\",\"postDate\":1471304264,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Frank Myers is a global payroll professional with over 25 years of experience. After retiring from the U.S. Navy in 2012, Frank was quickly recruited into the technology and gaming industry. His passion for improving and perfecting HR processes led him to Bridge Partners in early 2015. Frank is an expert in finance, travel, human resources, and logistics operations. Working in diverse settings, both stateside and in foreign currency organizations, Frank has improved HRIS\\/Payroll onboarding and management processes. He studied Business Administration at the University of Maryland, University College.\\n\\nFrank was born and raised in Seattle, Washington and has traveled to every continent of the world. \\u00a0When he isn\\u2019t nose-first in spreadsheets, you can find him spending time with his husband Jamey and their dog on the Washington Coast, singing along with his brothers in song with the world-renown Seattle Men\\u2019s Chorus or grabbing a bite to eat (and a luscious glass of wine) at any one of the myriad of great farm-to-table restaurants and bistros in the Seattle area.\",\"83\":\"frank.myers@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Frank_Myers.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Payroll Manager\",\"87\":\"Corporate Staff\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:44', '2016-08-15 23:37:44', 'e90fb5e0-c85b-4f48-82c0-a36298b6d36f'),
 ('239', '530', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Patrick Keating\",\"slug\":\"patrick-keating\",\"postDate\":1471304264,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Patrick is an accomplished business leader who helps companies achieve their business goals. He collaborates with clients to capture business requirements, develop the right strategies, and manage implementation and change management activities to deliver the desired outcomes.\\u00a0\\n\\nPatrick has led large service delivery organizations as Principal at Randstad Technologies and managed global solution teams as Global Director of Industry Solutions at Dell. Patrick has broad cross-industry experience and deep functional expertise spanning marketing, operations, sales, engineering, and program management.\\n\\nAs a thought leader in the mobile industry, Patrick has written many white papers, blogs, and thought leadership pieces focused on mobility strategies addressing access, wireless infrastructure, cloud-based application delivery, security, and implementation options.\\n\\nPatrick has three wonderful children that keep him sharp. He enjoys playing tennis, running, and biking.\\u00a0\",\"83\":\"patrick.keating@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Patrick-Keating.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:44', '2016-08-15 23:37:44', '6cfb9b20-b37f-4cb8-928b-4cc7daf14c23'),
 ('240', '531', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Belinda Ho\",\"slug\":\"belinda-ho\",\"postDate\":1471304264,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Belinda is an experienced project manager who has helped lead several successful software rollouts and technical projects.\\u00a0Detail oriented and a creative problem solver, she enjoys bringing clarity to complex business problems.\\u00a0With over six years of experience in operations, management, training, and process improvement for companies like Global Transportation Services and Microsoft, Belinda helps teams connect and communicate more effectively to streamline workflows and improve efficiencies.\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0\\nBelinda holds a Bachelors of Business Administration from Pacific Lutheran University, where she participated in three business-focused study abroad programs that took her all over China and Europe.\\n\\u00a0\\nIn her free time, she enjoys hosting dinner parties, traveling to new places, spending time with her family, and playing in a local kickball league.\",\"83\":\"belinda.ho@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Belinda-Ho.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Consultant\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:44', '2016-08-15 23:37:44', 'ff5889f9-c54b-4e41-b0ab-6bf970dcba05'),
 ('241', '532', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Lana Brooks\",\"slug\":\"lana-brooks\",\"postDate\":1471304264,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Lana is an experienced Human Resources professional who builds positive relationships with hiring managers and candidates. She started her career in HR in 2010 with the Federal Government at the Department of Defense and later was an integral part of the Recruiting teams with the State of Washington and Cox Enterprises.\\u00a0\\n\\nLana holds a graduate degree in HR from Brandman University and an undergraduate degree in Linguistics and Teaching from the Mordovian State University.\\n\\nWhen she\'s not looking for the best and brightest talent, Lana takes pleasure in learning new languages and staying proficient in the ones she has already acquired. She also enjoys trips to Europe and tropical destinations where she is always excited to meet people of diverse backgrounds.\",\"83\":\"lana.brooks@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Lana-Brooks.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Recruiter\",\"87\":\"Corporate Staff\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:44', '2016-08-15 23:37:44', 'fee8c0d1-7aba-409b-96ff-705370f6fdc1'),
 ('242', '533', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Chalea Conley\",\"slug\":\"chalea-conley\",\"postDate\":1471304264,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Chalea is a people-centric recruiting professional with more than seven years of experience in Talent Acquisition, Human Resources, and Staffing. She started her career at a Fortune 1000 staffing company where she held administrative, payroll, and recruiting positions.\\u00a0\\n\\nChalea works with professionals from a variety of industries including technology, telecom, healthcare, and non-profit. She has a passion for matching candidates with exciting and challenging opportunities as they grow their careers.\\u00a0\\n\\nAlong with her husband and daughter, Chalea spends her free time camping with friends, barbecuing at their cabin on Camano Island, and watching the Seahawks win.\\u00a0\\n\\nContact Chalea to learn about new opportunities with Bridge Partners!\",\"83\":\"chalea.conley@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Chalea-Conley.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Recruiter\",\"87\":\"Corporate Staff\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:45', '2016-08-15 23:37:45', '20bcd362-dcad-4991-b82a-2537e73c7b56'),
 ('243', '534', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Catherine Sazon\",\"slug\":\"catherine-sazon\",\"postDate\":1471304265,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Catherine\\u2019s ability to achieve results for her clients is driven by her strong background in program management and undeniable passion for technology. Her experience in the healthcare, aerospace, and technology have fostered an ability to learn and adapt in fast-paced environments while exceeding client expectations.\\u00a0\\n\\nWith a degree in marketing and international business from Seattle University, Catherine\\u2019s knowledge and skills are supplemented by work experience that encompasses not only program management, but campaign development and execution, SharePoint and creative design, and event management and execution.\\n\\u00a0\\nOutside of work, you can find Catherine on the flag football field with friends, cooking, or traveling \\u2013 doing just about anything that involves friends, family, and food.\",\"83\":\"catherine.sazon@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Catherine-Sazon.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Consultant\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:45', '2016-08-15 23:37:45', 'df3ece47-5637-4086-8f72-7c25b336ad06'),
 ('244', '535', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jessica Harbin\",\"slug\":\"jessica-harbin\",\"postDate\":1471304265,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Since settling in Seattle, Jessica has been working with high-tech clients like Microsoft, F5 Networks, Adobe and Cisco. \\u00a0She is experienced in business development, content creation and project management, and she is truly passionate about getting to know all of her clients and understanding their unique business challenges. \\u00a0She is adept at quickly distilling customer pain points and needs into distinct implementation plans that align to greater business strategy.\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0\\nWhile Jessica got her start in the Midwest, she considers herself a student of the world. \\u00a0Her years in journalism and media production took her around the world: from London and Washington, D.C. to Chicago and Bangkok. \\u00a0Even now, whenever reality allows, Jessica loves to travel near and far.\\n\\u00a0\\nJessica is a die-hard University of Michigan fan, and enjoys cheering on her Wolverines, even through the tough years. \\u00a0She is always eager to take advantage of the Seattle area\\u2019s natural beauty: whether it\\u2019s hiking the surrounding trails, or walking around Green Lake with friends.\\u00a0\",\"83\":\"jessica.harbin@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Jessica-Harbin.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Managing Consultant\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:45', '2016-08-15 23:37:45', '714c84fa-b027-4253-a5c5-da2a4a0448a0'),
 ('245', '536', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Hollie Peltier\",\"slug\":\"hollie-peltier1\",\"postDate\":1471304265,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Hollie is a seasoned marketing and sales professional with more than two decades of technology experience. She has spent 15 years in the cloud services space building strategies, implementing go-to-market programs, and driving successful outcomes for customers, partners, and field sales organizations. \\u00a0\\n\\u00a0\\nHollie is also a global product launch expert and has held key management positions at Samsung and Microsoft as well as high tech start-ups and mid-size businesses. She is a proven leader with a record of success managing worldwide marketing and product teams. Hollie is a highly versatile marketer and has served as the program, product marketing, and governance consulting leads for a number of Microsoft business units and for Seattle Children\\u2019s Hospital.\\u00a0\\n\\nHollie and her husband, Craig, moved to the Seattle area eight years ago from a sunny beach community in Southern California. They, along with their Boxer and Boston Terrier, are year-round Alpine wilderness hikers exploring the Cascade Mountains most weekends.\",\"83\":\"hollie.peltier@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Hollie_Peltier.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:45', '2016-08-15 23:37:45', '6253c578-ac32-4f9f-b478-db47c2d14acf'),
 ('246', '537', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Anthony Smith\",\"slug\":\"anthony-smith\",\"postDate\":1471304265,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Anthony admires balanced focus. As an organizational change management expert, he is engaged in asking clients three questions:\\u00a0\\n\\n\\n\\tDo you have a common framework, language, and set of tools for managing significant change?\\u00a0\\n\\tAre your plans for change integrated into overall project plans?\\u00a0\\n\\tWho is accountable for effective change management in your organization?\\n\\n\\nAnthony can show you what to say, how to say it, and the best avenues for execution and implementation. Known as a \\\"right-hand man,\\\" Anthony works with the best and brightest to discover actionable insights. Organizations like Microsoft have partnered with Anthony when they need an effective project manager and organizational listener with a genuine personality.\\u00a0\\n\\nAnthony has 7+ years of experience in general management and business development and a Masters in Organizational Development. In his free time, Anthony enjoys photography, hiking, and playing acoustic guitar. He volunteers for March of Dimes.\\u00a0\",\"83\":\"anthony.smith@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Anthony_Smith.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:45', '2016-08-15 23:37:45', '35b8df0f-969b-4a4d-aace-8e2a9fe4e6d1'),
 ('247', '538', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Matthew Albert\",\"slug\":\"matthew-albert\",\"postDate\":1471304265,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Matthew is an innovative marketing executive with 25 years of experience driving integrated marketing efforts across the Fortune 500. He has worked with\\u00a0brands like T-Mobile, Microsoft, AT&T, Disney, Best Buy, Anheuser-Busch, and many more. He brings real-world, pressure-tested skills to the Bridge Partners team, along with deep expertise across multiple communications platforms. He has successfully managed large-scale marketing programs and multi-billion dollar P&Ls.\\n\\nAreas of Expertise:\\u00a0\\n\\n\\n\\tBrand & Marketing Strategy\\n\\tIntegrated Marketing Programs\\n\\tCustomer-Centric Digital Experiences\\n\\tContent Marketing & Social Media\\n\\tData-Driven Decision Management\\n\\n\\nMatthew earned his BA in Advertising from the University of Florida, and then went on to complete his MBA at Nova. \\u00a0And when he\\u2019s not helping our clients optimize their digital experiences or drive deeper connections between sales and marketing, he\\u2019s enjoying the company of his wife and two little girls, cheering for his beloved Gators Football team, sharpening his culinary skills, or re-arranging his ever-growing wine collection (again).\",\"83\":\"matthew.albert@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Matt-Albert.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Digital Solutions Leader\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:45', '2016-08-15 23:37:45', '3514f4e9-fad2-4a75-b722-a95ef9c82a9a'),
 ('248', '539', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jan Weisel\",\"slug\":\"jan-weisel\",\"postDate\":1471304265,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Jan has over 20 years of experience as a content manager\\/developer. She has successfully managed content projects and developed both competitive field- and partner-ready content for diverse product and business groups throughout Microsoft.\\n\\nJan enjoys taking on new challenges and setting up new processes to streamline workflows. She was a strategic member of the team that created and launched the first Microsoft KnowledgeBase and wrote several hundred articles for this widely-used support tool. She has deep experience in delivering strong verbal and written internal\\/external communications using traditional and social media channels.\\n\\nAs a consultant, Jan is at her best managing diverse content-management projects and is able to use her strong project and technical skillset to ensure that projects are completed on time and under budget.\\u00a0\\n\\nOutside of work, Jan loves to explore new hikes with her dog, Boomer, and her husband, Land. She also loves to travel, bake, and try out new restaurants.\\u00a0\",\"83\":\"jan.weisel@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Jan-Weisel.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Consultant\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:45', '2016-08-15 23:37:45', '4b49332d-9175-4e76-afe6-85478e7be061'),
 ('249', '540', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jon Griffin\",\"slug\":\"jon-griffin\",\"postDate\":1471304265,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Jon has over 20 years of experience helping businesses keep and grow their greatest asset, satisfied customers. He is a skilled business analyst with deep expertise in operations, systems design and implementation, data management and governance, and database architecture.\\u00a0\\n\\nPrior to joining Bridge Partners, Jon held a variety of program and systems management roles at Microsoft, both as an employee and a contractor. He holds an MBA from Seattle University and an economics degree from Whitman College.\\u00a0\\n\\nAway from work, Jon enjoys spending time with his wife, Yolanda, and their three kids. He is a licensed pilot and flies as a hobby in his free time. \\u00a0 \\u00a0\",\"83\":\"jon.griffin@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Jon-Griffin.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:46', '2016-08-15 23:37:46', '329dfc39-fa23-4f66-9ff3-6b666ec132ae'),
 ('250', '541', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Stephanie Hescock\",\"slug\":\"stephanie-hescock\",\"postDate\":1471304266,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Stephanie brings over 10+ years of consulting and program management experience, primarily in the software and wireless telecom industries. She has managed complex large-scale web, sales &\\u00a0marketing, and product development initiatives. She spent 5 years in the marketing division of a high-tech software company managing corporate planning, campaign reporting, and strategic organizational development projects. She spent another 5+ years in ecommerce, working for a wireless telecom company, where she created and managed a PMO team.\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0\\nAway from work, Stephanie enjoys spending time with her two boys and husband, reading when she has a free moment, and exercising.\\u00a0\",\"83\":\"stephanie.hescock@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/stephanie-hescock-2.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Managing Consultant\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:46', '2016-08-15 23:37:46', '5d651243-87b0-4b9d-8a17-f6a0f002ea06'),
 ('251', '542', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Tim Tow\",\"slug\":\"tim-tow\",\"postDate\":1471304266,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Tim helps clients successfully execute transformation projects, derive actionable insight through strategic data analysis, and formulate business strategies to accelerate revenue growth and delight customers. \\u00a0He is passionate about increasing customer loyalty and improving operational efficiencies. \\u00a0Tim has a background in strategy, product management, data analytics, business intelligence, software development, and hardware manufacturing.\\u00a0\\n\\nTim holds an MBA from the McCombs School of Business at The University of Texas. \\u00a0In his spare time, he enjoys running, board gaming, and raising chickens.\",\"83\":\"tim.tow@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Tim-Tow.jpg\",\"86\":\"The PMO: Tax or Benefit?Planning for the Inevitable: A Proactive Change Approach\",\"82\":\"Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:46', '2016-08-15 23:37:46', '60c6dcdb-b52e-4d64-a0d2-55614a51941b'),
 ('252', '543', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Renee St Jacques\",\"slug\":\"renee-st-jacques1\",\"postDate\":1471304266,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Renee St Jacques is a business and marketing professional with nearly 11 years of Microsoft experience in marketing, product management, project management, product launches, event management, audience marketing, and online\\/digital marketing. She has helped lead over 6 product launches for the US subsidiary when she was a full time employee and spent the three years as a senior consultant working on the Windows 8 Retail business, EPG Audience Marketing and Cloud Marketing teams, and currently with the WW Partner Group. While fiercely passionate about excellence in her professional life, Renee is equally fervent in pursuing other passions in her personal life such as the arts, travel, and social justice work.\",\"83\":\"renee.stjacques@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Renee_St_Jacques_4.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Consultant\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:46', '2016-08-15 23:37:46', '9ef1d95b-4d29-4bc4-8015-8e16d8585201'),
 ('253', '544', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Tim Gunderson\",\"slug\":\"tim-gunderson\",\"postDate\":1471304266,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Tim is a skilled communicator and resourceful problem solver who approaches every project with a fresh perspective. He understands how to turn complex product features into clear messages that drive customer engagement. Clients benefit from his nuanced understanding of digital content strategy, sharp eye for detail, and creative thinking.\\u00a0\\n\\nIn addition to his consulting work, Tim also oversees marketing strategy and communications for Bridge. He is passionate about promoting the Bridge Partners brand and enjoys collaborating with thought leaders from across the firm.\\u00a0\\n\\nTim holds an MBA from Seattle University and a BA from the University of Washington. In his free time, he enjoys coaching and playing basketball, eating, travelling, and watching the Seahawks and Huskies.\\u00a0\",\"83\":\"tim.gunderson@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Tim-Gunderson-2.jpg\",\"86\":\"Cutting Through the Clutter: Visual Content Marketing\",\"82\":\"Senior Consultant\",\"87\":\"Corporate Staff\\n  Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:46', '2016-08-15 23:37:46', '98206c25-0480-428f-8fe8-f0f974566fd3'),
 ('254', '545', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Laura Noonan\",\"slug\":\"laura-noonan\",\"postDate\":1471304266,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Laura has 20 years of experience in marketing, with a focus in the tech sector. She\\u2019s held senior management positions with Microsoft, Hewlett-Packard, and Flexera Software. Laura\\u2019s areas of expertise include strategy, product and vertical marketing, demand generation, sales readiness, and complex pro-\\nject management.\\u00a0\\n\\nAs a consultant, Laura enjoys the variety and challenge of working with different clients to understand their business and help them craft and execute innovative business strategies. She likes to understand the big picture while digging into the details and excels at bringing complex technology products to market.\\nShe is passionate about working with clients to gain in-depth understanding\\nof their buyer in order to wield influence during the earliest stages of the\\nbuyer\\u2019s journey. Laura is proficient in leading marketing programs and strate-\\ngic communications with extensive experience in planning and business management, tracking goals, and managing large projects with multiple stakeholders.\\n\\nOriginally from Upstate New York, Laura is a graduate of State University of New York at Cortland and is now based in the Chicago area.\\u00a0In her free time you can find her skiing, hiking, or playing golf.\\u00a0She also enjoys traveling and spending time in the Adirondack Mountains.\",\"83\":\"laura.noonan@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Laura-Noonan.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:46', '2016-08-15 23:37:46', 'd35ea41c-d88c-44ea-b569-efb4506ae001'),
 ('255', '546', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Vignesh Karumbaya\",\"slug\":\"vignesh-karumbaya\",\"postDate\":1471304266,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Vignesh has 10+ years of experience in strategy, operations, and analytics. He has successfully built relationships with senior executives while managing internal and external clients and partners.\\n\\nVignesh has developed and deployed business solutions, operations strategies, and logistics and supply chain efficiencies for global clients across a broad spectrum of industries, from Fortune 500 companies to start\\u2010ups. He also has significant experience in analyzing target markets, customer segmentation, data analytics, and competitor benchmarking.\\n\\nVignesh received his MBA from the Ross School of Business at the University of Michigan, where he was also a Fellow at the Tauber Institute of Global Operations. Having lived on 4 continents, Vignesh loves to travel and is also an avid motorsport, film, and video game enthusiast. These days, he is exploring what Chicago can add to that list.\",\"83\":\"vignesh.karumbaya@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Vignesh-Karumbaya.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:46', '2016-08-15 23:37:46', '92770023-eb36-40b9-af0e-52eeb2bd3c7b'),
 ('256', '547', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Robin Nirken Berson\",\"slug\":\"robin-berson\",\"postDate\":1471304267,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Robin brings a unique 360-degree sales and marketing perspective to Bridge Partners. The range of roles she has had throughout her career have provided her with a holistic strategic view and effective implementation approach. After 7 years in advertising as a marketing consultant, Robin realized she had a passion for helping clients and solving business challenges.\\u00a0She progressed her career over the next 13 years at Dell, where she gained experience in partner marketing & sales programs, sales,\\u00a0global corporate development strategies, as well as online sales tools.\\u00a0While under the Dell umbrella, she was fortunate to work with\\u00a0companies in a variety of areas including\\u00a0education, technology, and government.\\n\\nRobin spends her personal time with her husband,\\u00a0daughter, and furry pup, Bella.\\u00a0She also volunteers for Keep Austin Fed, a local food rescue organization.\",\"83\":\"robin.berson@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Robin-Berson-2.jpg\",\"86\":\"Why I Joined Bridge Partners\",\"82\":\"Director\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:47', '2016-08-15 23:37:47', '48b94cc7-6443-49d3-a011-58206c4acd92'),
 ('257', '548', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"McKenzie Huneke\",\"slug\":\"mckenzie-huneke\",\"postDate\":1471304267,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"McKenzie is fascinated by solving challenges that cross technology, user needs, communication, and business factors. With over 10 years of experience in product management, marketing, and consulting, he applies a user-centered research & design approach to help companies create and maintain meaningful relationships with customers. He has provided strategy, research, planning, marketing, and information design for clients including Intel, HP, Dell, Microsoft, Cisco, and EMC.\\n\\nMcKenzie holds a BA from UC Berkeley and a MS in Human Centered Design & Engineering from University of Washington, where his National Science Foundation-sponsored academic research contributions on engineering design thinking were published by IEEE.\\n\\nIn his free time, McKenzie enjoys competitive swimming, cycling around the Northwest, and playing classical & jazz piano.\",\"83\":\"mckenzie.huneke@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Mckenzie-Huneke.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Consultant\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:47', '2016-08-15 23:37:47', 'f5eb3aea-a1c7-413c-bf16-3ea827d91319'),
 ('258', '549', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jennifer Kerns\",\"slug\":\"jennifer-kerns\",\"postDate\":1471304267,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Jennifer is a technical writer and editor who has 20 years\' experience in the software industry. As a writer\\/editor, she takes pride in helping customers organize their thoughts and present their ideas in a clear and concise fashion. In addition to writing and editing herself, Jennifer has had considerable success managing teams of writers and editors and acting as a mentor to new writers, in particular to people for whom English is a second (or third!) language.\",\"83\":\"jennifer.kerns@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Jennifer-Kerns.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:47', '2016-08-15 23:37:47', '76a44d8d-945c-4e84-8079-2524208b377b'),
 ('259', '550', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Catherine Deis\",\"slug\":\"catherine-deis\",\"postDate\":1471304267,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Catherine is a people-centric professional, with over nine years of experience in recruiting, training and human resources.\\u00a0She has helped companies grow by 40%, year over year, by finding the best and brightest talent.\\u00a0Half of her professional experience has focused specifically on continuous improvement, where she acted as an internal consultant to improve process efficien-\\ncies.\\u00a0Catherine has worked in the technology, entertainment, and digital advertising industries.\\u00a0Whatever role she has taken on, Catherine always maintains a genuine interest in people and a strong drive for delivering results.\\u00a0\\n\\nOutside of work, Catherine spends much of her free time playing with her family at the park, or reading up on her newest hobby, interior design.\\u00a0She also enjoys trying new restaurants with her husband and friends. \\u00a0\\u00a0\",\"83\":\"catherine.deis@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Catherine-Deis.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Recruiter\",\"87\":\"Corporate Staff\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:47', '2016-08-15 23:37:47', 'f0a2a277-7186-4ff3-ba6e-6902f3206e02'),
 ('260', '551', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Dave Friant\",\"slug\":\"dave-friant\",\"postDate\":1471304267,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Dave has 30+ years of experience in the computer software and hardware business. Throughout his career Dave has held a number of senior-level and director-level positions within three main disciplines: 1) computer-aided-design and manufacturing systems; 2) biometric authentication and identification systems; and 3) security development lifecycle compliance and regulatory compliance audit preparation. For the past 7 years Dave has spent his time working at Microsoft as a Senior Program Manager and as a consultant for regulatory audit preparation.\\n\\nAs a consultant Dave enjoys the variety of projects that he is exposed to where he can draw from his experience to drive and manage projects to completion on-time and within budget. Dave thrives in being able to increase organizational effectiveness through ongoing process improvements. For example, while at Microsoft Dave successfully reorganized the FIPS 140-2 certification of the Windows Operating System Cryptography Modules in parallel with new releases of the Windows OS. This process improvement resulted in multi-millions of dollars in revenue to be realized by Microsoft from its largest customer, the US government, immediately upon release of a new version of Windows.\\n\\nDave is also an accomplished design engineer, having designed a number of kayak-style cardboard boats he wrote \'The Cardboard Boat Book\', or How to Build an Environmentally-Friendly Boat with Recyclable Resources. The Cardboard Boat Book is in 160 of the countries in the world. Dave has earned a US patent for a disposable reading lens. Dave also designs, builds, and fly\'s remotely-piloted sailplanes, he is an avid boater and loves to spend time traveling with his wife.\",\"83\":\"dave.friant@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Dave-Friant.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:47', '2016-08-15 23:37:47', 'f9e17631-bbc5-471d-939e-a25ce3dd24c1'),
 ('261', '552', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Dominic Fleming\",\"slug\":\"dominic-fleming\",\"postDate\":1471304267,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Dom\\u00a0Tor\\u00a0Fleming is a finance and strategy leader with 20+ years of experience in finance, management, and business consulting.\\u00a0Dom has broad global experience in financial planning, analysis, and controllership as well as in performance management, reporting, and project management in large enterprises, midsized organizations, and\\u00a0startups.\\u00a0Dom has a focused interest at the intersection of organizational management, finance, and strategy, with expertise in connecting business strategies to specific metric goals to drive accountability and performance throughout the organization.\\n\\nDom\\u00a0received his MBA from the University of Chicago Graduate School of Business with focuses in Finance, Strategic Management, and Organization and Behavioral Management. He\\u00a0was magna cum laude at the University of Illinois with a BA\\u00a0in International Trade and German Language.\\u00a0He is also a\\u00a0Project Management Professional (PMP) as certified by the Project Management Institute (PMI).\\n\\nDom lives in Anacortes, Washington with wife and son, where he is active in the community and travels frequently.\\u00a0Dom\\u00a0spends his spare time hiking, rock climbing, training for triathlons, and adventuring with his family in the mountains and along the ocean.\\n\\n\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0\",\"83\":\"dom.fleming@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Dominic-Fleming.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Chief Financial Officer\",\"87\":\"Leadership\\n  Corporate Staff\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:47', '2016-08-15 23:37:47', '0647a61c-78fd-48ba-8730-1dfb0ac1eb38'),
 ('262', '553', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Nathan Wright\",\"slug\":\"nathan-wright\",\"postDate\":1471304267,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"With 18+ years experience creating and implementing integrated marketing, communications, and process improvement plans, Nathan is passionate about helping companies increase revenue and value.\\u00a0His experience spans manufacturing, technology, retail, and public sector industries. He\\u2019s skilled at helping companies chart paths to success, and his combination of client-side and agency marketing experience helps him align business strategy across teams and organizations. \\u00a0\\n\\nHis pursuit of positive outcomes and results drive him toward innovative and disciplined project approaches that keep the quality of customer and partner\\nexperiences at the forefront of his thinking.\\u00a0He\\u00a0communicates skillfully, delivers\\u00a0great value, and thrives at building order from chaos.\\n\\nAreas of Expertise:\\n\\n\\n\\tMarketing and Communications Strategy\\n\\tValue Proposition, Positioning, and Messaging Development\\n\\tCustomer Segmentation and Persona Development\\n\\tSales Enablement and Buyer Journey Programs\\n\\tPartnership and Alliance Marketing\\n\\tProcess and Information Flow Development\\n\\n\\nPrior to joining Bridge Partners, Nathan led an agency practice and directed business operations for a Seattle technology marketing agency. Nathan holds a B.S. degree from the University of Maryland University College.\\u00a0He lives in Woodinville, WA with his wife and two children.\",\"83\":\"nathan.wright@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Nathan-Wright.jpg\",\"86\":\"Marketing Automation: Consistency Counts\",\"82\":\"Practice Lead\",\"87\":\"Leadership\\n  Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:48', '2016-08-15 23:37:48', 'ab35c634-ab97-468f-a7a8-68db32e6b9a0'),
 ('263', '554', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Basharat Khan\",\"slug\":\"basharat-khan\",\"postDate\":1471304268,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Basharat is an MBA who has successfully led and managed large-scale, complex initiatives for over ten years. He has experience formulating, launching, and executing CRM strategy. Before migrating to the United States, he was the head of Etisalat\\u2019s Group Support Center, which had 9 teams with 134 reps delivering support to 24 million subscribers.\\n\\nBasharat\\u2019s son and two daughters keep him busy when he is at home. He is also an active volunteer, participating in regular community events at AMI Seattle. Basharat has led thrilling high-altitude expeditions (over 14,000 ft) with \\\"Team Unimog\\\" in the Himalayas and Karakoram Mountains.\\u00a0\",\"83\":\"basharat.khan@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Basharat-Khan.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Sr. Manager Operations & IT Support\",\"87\":\"Corporate Staff\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:48', '2016-08-15 23:37:48', 'd5ecd5c4-68d6-42e8-85ff-b1f46d35c5be'),
 ('264', '555', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Razzia Walli\",\"slug\":\"razzia-walli\",\"postDate\":1471304268,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Razzia has a strong mix of project management and technical experience. She started her career as a software developer at IBM in New York State.\\u00a0This was followed by many years working in Information Technology and Product Development at Motorola and other high-tech companies.\\n\\nRazzia\\u2019s areas of expertise include Project Management, Product Development, Systems Integration & Operations, Business Analysis, Technical Writing and Process Improvement.\\n\\nRazzia enjoys the challenge of delivering complex and analytical projects that require attention to detail.\\u00a0Most recently at Microsoft, Razzia worked in the Global Partner Services (GPS) group and participated in the launch of the Partner Support Community (online forums which provide program and product support to thousands of Microsoft Partners).\\n\\nRazzia was born and raised in Dar-es-Salaam, Tanzania and has lived in the Middle East, India and Canada before settling in Seattle.\\n\\nRazzia stays busy outside work with reading, cooking, and travelling.\",\"83\":\"razzia.walli@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Razzia-Walli.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:48', '2016-08-15 23:37:48', '162fdb71-43f9-4694-9c3b-addb15695cd7'),
 ('265', '556', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Cristofer Munson\",\"slug\":\"cristofer-munson\",\"postDate\":1471304268,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"With over 19 years of experience in business and technology consulting, Cristofer is a seasoned leader with a proven track record of developing strong partnerships with clients, employees, and even competitors. Cristofer has a demonstrated ability to help executives, managers, and teams break down complex problems into their component parts from which a future state solution can be defined, designed, developed, and deployed. A skilled facilitator and communicator, Cristofer works easily across multiple teams at all levels within an organization to design solutions based on solid business strategy and purpose supported by achievable, measurable business goals and objectives.\\n\\nPrior to joining Bridge Partners, Cristofer was the founder and principal of the consulting firm Sound Perspectives Solutions Group.\\u00a0Cristofer was also a Senior Manager with Ernst & Young Management Consulting and Regional Director of Professional Services with E.piphany, Inc.\\n\\nCristofer is a magna cum laude, Phi Beta Kappa graduate from the University of Washington and holds Certificates in both Project Management and Software Product Management from the University of Washington.\",\"83\":\"cristofer.munson@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Cristofer-Munson.jpg\",\"86\":\"Putting the Drama in Project Management Part 1Putting the Drama in Project Management Part 2Putting the Drama in Project Management Part 3\",\"82\":\"Director\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:48', '2016-08-15 23:37:48', 'e67b8c82-1670-4e31-b2bb-0d8b457c7ec8'),
 ('266', '557', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Michelle Meyer\",\"slug\":\"michelle-meyer\",\"postDate\":1471304268,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Michelle has over ten years of professional experience with the past five focused in Project Management.\\u00a0She currently holds her PMP certification and is versatile in both agile and waterfall project management methodologies.\\u00a0She has experience in setting up a PMO and establishing project management disciplines within product development and marketing.\\u00a0She has expertise in supporting product launches, web campaigns, and special events.\\u00a0\\n\\nAs a consultant, Michelle excels at influencing without direct authority, establishing clear communication channels, building relationships, and process improvement. She enjoys the challenge of leading cross-functional projects with multiple stakeholder personalities, establishing strong relationships and improving project performance.\\u00a0Michelle has worked for Bona US (Hardwood Floor Industry), Artitudes Design (Microsoft Vendor) and T-Mobile.\\n\\nMichelle and her husband spend weekends chasing around their two young daughters.\\u00a0She also was a college athlete and still plays basketball.\\u00a0\",\"83\":\"michelle.meyer@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Michelle-Meyer.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Consultant\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:48', '2016-08-15 23:37:48', '884fb204-7063-4c9a-9d87-32de219e71ef'),
 ('267', '558', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Thomas Doggett\",\"slug\":\"thomas-b.-doggett\",\"postDate\":1471304268,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Tom\\u00a0is a highly experienced technology executive with two decades of proven success building, launching, and advising early-stage and\\u00a0established techn-\\nology companies. He is known for exceptional capabilities in creating and executing focused go-to-market launches that\\u00a0integrate sales, marketing, and channel strategies with one goal in mind: drive revenue.\\n\\nAs a 20-year student of technology markets and their evolution, Tom is passion-\\nate about identifying and developing unique solution offerings that meet changing customer needs. He is highly effective in leading world-class sales, marketing, and PR teams and serving as a trusted advisor for numerous Fortune 100 companies.\\n\\nPrior to joining\\u00a0Bridge Partners, Tom co-founded Calico Energy, an energy management software company serving the energy sector. As CMO, he implemented highly successful sales, marketing, and channel partner programs. Prior to Calico, Tom was a principal at BuzzBee Company, a Seattle-based marketing consulting firm. While at BuzzBee, he helped Fortune 100 companies bring enterprise-class software products and services to market. Tom previously led the Marketing, PR, and Investor Relations team at Saflink, a leading publicly-held security and access control software company. Prior to Saflink, he consulted with Fortune 100 firms \\u2013 including IDC, SAP, Siemens, and Nike \\u2013 on marketing and technology initiatives. Tom holds an MBA in Technology Marketing from Babson College and a Master\\u2019s Certificate in Sustainable Business from Bainbridge Graduate Institute.\\n\\nIn his time away from work, Tom is an avid outdoor enthusiast, and enjoys hunting and fishing with his friends and family. He also serves as Board President of Three Cedars Waldorf School, where his two daughters attend.\",\"83\":\"tom.doggett@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Thomas-B.-Doggett.jpg\",\"86\":\"Developing a Dynamic Approach to Digital Marketing\",\"82\":\"Director\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:48', '2016-08-15 23:37:48', '884e62e5-37f8-468e-a0f4-2571ccd97b7c'),
 ('268', '559', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jim Sloane\",\"slug\":\"jim-sloane\",\"postDate\":1471304269,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Jim is a strategic thinker with more than 20 years of technology experience in consulting, sales, product development and network engineering with Fortune 100 companies like Microsoft, US WEST, Key Bank, Boeing and numerous other organizations in technology, healthcare, financial services, manufacturing\\nand retail.\\n\\nJim is a business technology consultant with a reputation for being a global leader, solving complex problems and meeting business needs in a timely and economical manner. Most recently, he has worked with the Microsoft Engineering, Community and Online (ECO) organization as a program manager rolling out of a new software application to Microsoft\\u2019s worldwide call center vendors.\\u00a0He is experienced working on and being a part of global teams.\\n\\nJim graduated from the University of Washington with a degree in Engineering. On his off time, you\\u2019ll find him and his wife spending time with their two sons, family and friends. They enjoy outdoor activities including hiking in the Cascades, skiing at Crystal Mountain, camping and travel.\",\"83\":\"jim.sloane@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Jim-Sloane.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:49', '2016-08-15 23:37:49', '66d59e43-ecce-4ea7-bfb6-eea3d9b32f4c'),
 ('269', '560', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jerry Leishman\",\"slug\":\"jerry-leishman\",\"postDate\":1471304269,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"For 25+ years, Jerry has helped organizations transform ideas into world class products and solutions.\\u00a0 He is a passionate, collaborative, results-oriented thought leader and executor who has worked in consumer and commercial product management and IT leadership roles. He has a track record of successfully envisioning, building, launching, and selling\\u00a0innovative solutions, products, and technologies.\\u00a0Jerry also has\\u00a0extensive experience directly managing teams that span the\\u00a0full software and solution development lifecycle across functions, organizations, and geographies.\\n\\nAreas of Expertise:\\n\\n\\n\\tCloud Computing (SaaS, PaaS, and IaaS)\\n\\tIT Governance, Risk, &\\u00a0Compliance (IT GRC)\\n\\tSecurity & System Management\\n\\tCustomer Contact Centers (CRM)\\n\\tIT Service Management (ITSM)\\n\\n\\nJerry received his MBA\\u00a0from Southern Methodist University and his BS and BA from the University of Puget Sound in Computer Science and Business Administration, respectively.\",\"83\":\"jerry.leishman@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Jerry-Leishman.jpg\",\"86\":\"CIO: What\\u2019s Your Value Chain for Cloud Transformation?Selling Cloud Solutions to Government Agencies\",\"82\":\"Director\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:49', '2016-08-15 23:37:49', '9721fb62-ffac-4750-b5fe-451142f75775'),
 ('270', '561', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Ksenija Pergar\",\"slug\":\"ksenija-pergar1\",\"postDate\":1471304269,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Ksenija is a senior Project Manager with 20+ years of experience in business and marketing management in the IT and travel industries. Throughout her career, Ksenija has successfully managed complex marketing projects while adeptly solving problems across multiple functional teams and geographies. She is passionate about building relationships, supporting teams, and enabling them to achieve results.\\n\\nBorn and raised in Slovenia, Ksenija has worked and lived in many places in Europe and the United States. When she moved with her husband to Seattle in 2006, she interrupted a successful career in the travel industry, not realizing, at the time, the doors that would be opened to boundless new experiences. Upon arriving in the Northwest, she began consulting at Microsoft. She appreciates the freedom she has to leverage her creativity and resourcefulness.\\u00a0Her understanding of world cultures continues to serve her well as she works with diverse teams.\\n\\nKsenija currently lives in the Seattle area with her family. She\\u2019s an outdoor enthusiast who enjoys travelling around the world, but also loves finding peace in her garden of flowers.\",\"83\":\"ksenija.pergar@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Ksenija-Pergar.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:49', '2016-08-15 23:37:49', 'bda28f24-289b-41cc-a864-5cc07c501147'),
 ('271', '562', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Susan Dodds\",\"slug\":\"susan-dodds\",\"postDate\":1471304269,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Susan is a customer-centric marketing leader with experience in product marketing, program planning, and global operations spanning technology, financial services and retail industries. She has proven success driving optimization strategies, expanding customer relationships and achieving business growth objectives through marketing programs and operational improvements.\\n\\nHighly effective at cross group collaboration, communications, problem solving, and ability to influence executive decisions, Susan creates solutions that yield a high rate of return. She is also very practiced at leading social media strategy and presence, delivering effective branding strategies, and campaigns for Fortune 500 technology and financial services corporations.\\n\\nOriginally from the East Coast (New Jersey to be precise), Susan feels most at home here on the West Coast. She is an avid yogi, a tutor for underprivileged, at-risk youth, and enjoys travelling, reading and wine.\",\"83\":\"susan.dodds@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Susan-Dodds.jpg\",\"86\":\"Look Before You Leap: Planning for Social Media Success\",\"82\":\"Managing Consultant\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:49', '2016-08-15 23:37:49', '16cd4403-61d2-4390-8877-df491c2264b3'),
 ('272', '563', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Laurie Baars\",\"slug\":\"laurie-baars\",\"postDate\":1471304269,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Laurie has 15+ years of experience in marketing, with a focus in the telecom and tech sectors. She\\u2019s held senior marketing manager positions with AT&T, Nuance Communications, and Varolii Corporation. Laurie\\u2019s areas of expertise include strategy, product marketing, sales readiness, marketing communications, branding, and complex project management.\\u00a0\\n\\nAs a consultant, Laurie enjoys the variety and challenge of working with different clients to understand their needs and help them improve processes and results. She likes to understand the big picture while digging into the details and excels at bringing complex technology products to market.\\n\\nOriginally from Texas, she has a BBA in Marketing from the University of Texas. In her free time you can find her hiking and cross country skiing with her husband and dog or getting creative with a pen and sketchbook.\",\"83\":\"laurie.baars@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Laurie-Baars.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:49', '2016-08-15 23:37:49', 'dc7f398e-9c16-42b5-ad77-88ce78c58c53'),
 ('273', '564', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Matt Hansink\",\"slug\":\"matt-hansink1\",\"postDate\":1471304269,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Matt is a seasoned project manager with over 15 years of marketing experience in both the technology and nonprofit fields. He has led various marketing programs for Microsoft including work with Azure, SharePoint, Worldwide Public Sector and Dynamics, and at F5 Networks in the high-growth communication service provider market. He has deep experience in corporate sales and co-founded QRate.com, one of the earliest innovators in web personalization and recommendation technologies.\\n\\u00a0\\nAs a consultant, Matt is at his best making complex or technical concepts widely accessible, while his background in sales and philanthropy help him identify opportunities for collaboration. Most importantly, he seeks to solve business challenges with creativity and unconventional thinking. He holds a BA in Marketing from Santa Clara University.\\n\\u00a0\\nMatt, his wife Holly, and four-year-old son Quinton, stay busy riding the Monorail, walking the dog, and visiting the Oregon coast.\",\"83\":\"matt.hansink@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Matt-Hansink.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:49', '2016-08-15 23:37:49', 'c0d59b04-5fcd-4806-96d2-a9bf32ab1aea'),
 ('274', '565', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kathy Chung\",\"slug\":\"kathy-chung1\",\"postDate\":1471304270,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Kathy brings over 10 years of consulting and project management experience to her clients in a wide range of industries including financial services, non-profit, software, and wireless telecom.\\u00a0Within these industries Kathy has delivered sales, marketing and software development projects.\\u00a0\\n\\nShe is known for her acute attention to detail, process oriented approach to problem solving, and collaborative communication style.\\u00a0Kathy holds a BA in History from Boston College.\\n\\nWhen not on a project Kathy is an avid rock climber with a deep passion for outdoor adventures.\\u00a0She has spent many seasons in Yosemite, Canyonlands, North Cascades and other national parks.\\u00a0You can find her scaling a mountain or on a local trail running with her Rhodesian Ridgeback.\",\"83\":\"kathy.chung@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Kathy-Chung.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:50', '2016-08-15 23:37:50', '3eeabcd7-9221-41f7-8d12-459bdfedf25b'),
 ('275', '566', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Susan Stanton\",\"slug\":\"susan-stanton\",\"postDate\":1471304270,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Susan has over 25 years in Sales and Recruiting Management and Business Development.\\u00a0She started her career with Revlon in New England then moved to Washington and was in the Wireless Industry managing sales teams for\\nover a\\u00a0decade.\\u00a0She shifted industries and moved into staffing in 2002 where she lead several top performing recruiting and sales teams at a Fortune 1000\\nstaffing company.\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0\\nSusan\\u2019s passion is consulting and matching highly talented, super smart people to projects that capitalize on their passions.\\u00a0When she\\u2019s not working you can find her spending time with family and friends, listening to her son jam on the guitar or cheering\\u00a0for our\\u00a0Super Bowl Champion\\u00a0Seahawks!\\n\\u00a0\\nAsk Susan about bringing your amazing skills to Bridge Partners\\u2026\\n\\u00a0\",\"83\":\"susan.stanton@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Susan-Stanton2.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Director of Talent\",\"87\":\"Leadership\\n  Corporate Staff\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:50', '2016-08-15 23:37:50', '2072d831-ef4e-4cac-87ee-b2b17906de4b'),
 ('276', '567', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Charles Kwon\",\"slug\":\"charles-kwon\",\"postDate\":1471304270,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Charles is a senior business consultant and executive with over 25 years of experience in transforming companies to maximize their value through growth strategies, new business models, increasing sales, and marketing & channel effectiveness.\\u00a0He has a proven track record of turning around and repositioning companies to\\u00a0maximize\\u00a0their value.\\u00a0\\n\\nCharles is also recognized for his ability to accelerate the development of\\nnew growth engines and businesses. He\\u00a0possesses strong strategy, general management, marketing, sales, and partner channel expertise, and has extensive experience in the high\\u00a0technology, automotive, industrial, aerospace, and\\u00a0consumer industries.\\u00a0Charles received his MBA from the Kellogg School of Management at Northwestern University, where he was an F. C. Austin Scholar, and\\u00a0obtained his BS in Mechanical Engineering from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology, where he was a Clapp and Poliak Design Scholar.\\n\\nIn his free time, Charles enjoys practicing Kendo and Brazilian Jiu Jitsu, as well as outdoor sports, such as\\u00a0skiing, cycling, and golf.\\u00a0He also enjoys traveling with his wife, Susan, and their two children, Matthew and Kiley.\",\"83\":\"charles.kwon@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Charles-Kwon.jpg\",\"86\":\"Riding the Big Bang: Winning in a World of Constant Disruption\",\"82\":\"Managing Director\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:50', '2016-08-15 23:37:50', 'a5849f7f-71c3-4961-8493-f499e90adb18'),
 ('277', '568', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Todd Vold\",\"slug\":\"todd-vold\",\"postDate\":1471304270,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Todd has proven experience tackling the toughest business problems. He brings decades of experience in project and program management, reporting strategy, process optimization, organizational design, and customer relationship manage-\\nment. Having worked in many sectors, from international freight forwarding to customer service and training, Todd brings fresh perspective and a methodical approach to drive real value for organizations.\\n\\nAs a Partner at Bridge, Todd\\u2019s passion for excellence and leadership create an environment that put his project teams on the cutting edge.\\n\\nTodd holds a degree in economics from the University of Colorado at Boulder. Todd loves meeting new people and travelling.\\u00a0You can find Todd on the side-\\nlines,\\u00a0coaching and cheering on his two sons, or on the river trying to trick a fish into his net at the nearest fishing hole.\",\"83\":\"todd.vold@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Todd-Vold.jpg\",\"86\":\"Turning the Dial to \\u2018Always On\\u2019 Sales Readiness\",\"82\":\"Partner\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:50', '2016-08-15 23:37:50', 'a3d7708e-fe15-4b3b-8aa6-b06c0a7a0573'),
 ('278', '569', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Richard Albrecht\",\"slug\":\"rich-albrecht\",\"postDate\":1471304270,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Rich has driven world-class marketing, strategy, and management initiatives in the technology, manufacturing, retail, and entertainment sectors. If your organization needs an advisor with a broad outlook and holistic, entrepreneurial approach, he\'ll open up new ways to analyze, plan, communicate, and execute.\\n\\nRich holds an Honors MBA from the University of Washington and a summa cum laude management degree from Seattle University.\\n\\nIn his spare time, you might find Rich pursuing his passion for off-the-grid wilderness adventures or coaching his sons\' basketball and soccer teams\\u2014and he keeps his Guitar Hero street cred fresh by playing with the legendary Seattle rock and roll band, Sweet Water.\",\"83\":\"richard.albrecht@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Rich-Albrecht.jpg\",\"86\":\"Partners for a Stronger CommunityRelationship Marketing: How Trust Works in a Digital WorldHow to Put Customers First in a Digital WorldWhy Austin?Let\'s Get Personal: Building Better B2B BrandsWelcome to Bridge Insights\",\"82\":\"CEO and Managing Partner\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:50', '2016-08-15 23:37:50', '72380069-56ea-49d1-93f2-157f2457e0ad'),
 ('279', '570', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Erin Russell Wieland\",\"slug\":\"erin-wieland\",\"postDate\":1471304270,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Erin is an experienced project manager with proficiency in customer engagement, event management and process improvement. Prior to consulting, she worked for a regional media marketing company, driving outreach strategy to improve product saturation in their core audience. With her strong background in customer engagement, Erin has been able to create valuable program connections and leverage experience to increase metrics.\\n\\nErin loves learning about new technologies and processes. She is passionate about marketing and improving business strategy and is motivated to combine those with her creative skills to provide valuable contributions to a team.\\n\\nIn her free time, Erin enjoys snowboarding, traveling and cooking.\",\"83\":\"erin.wieland@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Erin-Russell-Wieland.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:50', '2016-08-15 23:37:50', '468e4c2f-b187-487b-8595-aa366c95b0bd'),
 ('280', '571', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Barbara Spear\",\"slug\":\"barbara-spear\",\"postDate\":1471304270,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"A writer, editor, and project manager, Barbara has worked for Bridge Partners since 2011. She is a wordsmith and veteran consultant who has delivered messaging frameworks and created content for some of the biggest names in business. Barbara is passionate about working behind the scenes to help clients and colleagues accomplish their goals. She has also, to name a few former professions, written cookware catalogs, marketed wine, and run a professional theatre company.\\u00a0\\n\\nBarbara is happiest when traveling in Europe or indulging in one of her Martha-esque hobbies--cooking an ambitious menu, baking indulgent cookies, or handcrafting something colorful. She lives in Ballard with her husband, Taru.\",\"83\":\"barbara.spear@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Barbara-Spear.jpg\",\"86\":\"Filling in the Blanks: Brainstorming With Yourself\",\"82\":\"Senior Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:50', '2016-08-15 23:37:50', '77f8e471-1ae0-4c6f-9320-432c85896f1f'),
 ('281', '572', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Susmita Sharma\",\"slug\":\"susmita-sharma\",\"postDate\":1471304271,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Susmita brings over 15 years of experience in account management and project management at a wide variety of companies including Qwest Communications, Network Commerce, and Merck & Co. Susmita has held a variety of functional roles in her career and has the acumen and flexibility to succeed in high stress environments and fit into diverse teams.\\n\\nShe holds an MS in Molecular Biology from The Ohio State University and an MBA from the University of Washington. She is married and is the mother of two energetic young boys.\",\"83\":\"susmita.sharma@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Susmita-Sharma.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Manager\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', 'd9e85cc2-ca87-42a5-b728-52fff3ac8558'),
 ('282', '573', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Greg Proulx\",\"slug\":\"greg-proulx\",\"postDate\":1471304271,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Greg is a senior business executive with more than 25 years of experience growing direct revenue and partner-leveraged businesses at technology firms including HP, Oracle, and Microsoft. His cross-disciplinary experience benefits clients in partner and channel development, business strategy and planning, and field operations.\\n\\nAs General Manager of Microsoft\'s US Enterprise Partner business, Greg was responsible for a large managed partner ecosystem of over 500 global, regional, and local partners. He is highly effective communicating with execu-\\ntives, collaborating across groups, driving influence without authority, and\\u00a0instilling trust in teams.\\n\\nA computer engineering graduate from UCLA, Greg relishes time spent with his family, enjoying the outdoors around Puget Sound or travelling around the world. Look for him training for triathlons or team challenges like the Nike Hood\\u00a0to Coast or the Ragnar Relay Series.\",\"83\":\"greg.proulx@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Greg-Proulx.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Partner\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', 'e13674eb-0bf7-4ace-872d-27c8148e60fe'),
 ('283', '574', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Tania Fernandez de Castro\",\"slug\":\"tania-fernandez-de-castro\",\"postDate\":1471304271,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Tania has worked in the technology, government, manufacturing, and\\u00a0education sectors for over 18 years. Her multi-industry experience and approach has been a key factor in her ability to clearly understand business challenges, priorities, and drivers to deliver well-thought-out business solutions for her clients.\\n\\nShe has\\u00a0built and managed programs in technical and non-technical marketing, sales experience,\\u00a0enablement for\\u00a0internal and external audience, training, and social\\/community engagement.\\n\\nAreas of Expertise:\\n\\n\\n\\tField and Partner Enablement Programs\\n\\tSales Excellence - Account Planning\\n\\tProcess Improvement and Optimization\\n\\tGlobal Product Launch Programs\\n\\tProject Management\\n\\tConnected Sales and Marketing Programs\\n\\tProduct\\/Solution Marketing\\n\\n\\nRecent Highlights:\\n\\n\\n\\tDeveloped the\\u00a0SQL Server 2012 3-year Technical Readiness Strategy\\n\\tRedesigned the entire operations and communication strategy for a global technology corporation\\n\\tDeveloped and managed\\u00a0campaigns of\\u00a0local, state, and federal governments, including Gov. Gregoire 2010 Whistler Olympics Taskforce\\n\\n\\nBorn and raised in Mexico, Tania holds a Political Science degree from The Evergreen State College. She is fluent in Spanish and also speaks conversational Portuguese.\",\"83\":\"tania.f.decastro@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Tania-Fernandez-de-Castro.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Director\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '9fd29801-b269-4321-a8ad-3536d57a27fd'),
 ('284', '575', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Ezra Fain\",\"slug\":\"ezra-fain\",\"postDate\":1471304271,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Ezra\'s experience spans multiple industries including technology, communi-\\ncations, financial services, aerospace, and consumer packaged goods with firms such as Microsoft, T-Mobile, and Boeing. He is intrisically motivated to work on projects that change the way people think\\u00a0about their business and the work they do.\\n\\nEzra has a deep set of skills and experience in building programs to enable a \\u201cCompete\\u201d muscle across an enterprise. He understands how market forces and\\nbusiness models can work for or against an enterprise and brings a keen sense of how internal structures can drive competitive success. Ezra has a background in strategy, marketing, operations, finance, and process engineering.\\n\\nEzra\\u2019s loves boating, fishing and travel.\",\"83\":\"ezra.fain@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Ezra-Fain.jpg\",\"86\":\"Five Keys to Building a Compete Culture\",\"82\":\"Director\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', 'dd983c7a-9fa4-419a-9102-49a479a44fed'),
 ('285', '576', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Blair J. Foerster\",\"slug\":\"blair-j.-foerster\",\"postDate\":1471304271,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Blair is a seasoned project manager with a track record of successful engagements in online advertising, human resources, and competitive strategy. Prior to his consulting career, he worked for a Fortune 500 service bureau as account manager in business-to-business sales, where he specialized in cultivating relationships with CPA firms.\\n\\nHe is passionate about sales, marketing, and business strategy. Being tested with a steep learning curve and attaining confidence in new subject matter excites and motivates Blair for each new day. He holds a BA in Business Administration from the University of San Diego and earned an MBA from Seattle University.\\n\\nIn his free time, Blair loves outdoor activities such as fishing, hunting, skiing, and hiking. He also enjoys traveling with his wife Sarah and experiencing diverse cultures in countries around the globe.\",\"83\":\"blair.foerster@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Blair-Foerster.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Managing Consultant\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '181b41b5-a6dc-4b07-9352-d06cfba53d31'),
 ('286', '577', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Chase Morgan\",\"slug\":\"chase-morgan\",\"postDate\":1471304271,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Whether your sales strategy needs retooling or you want to expand and extend your partner alliances, Chase has the breadth of vision to make it happen. With more than 20 years of success building strategies and driving complex sales for organizations such as Microsoft, Siebel Systems, and IBM, Chase\\u2019s focus is on profitable sales excellence and world-class teams. Her smart, outside-the-box approach yields big results.\\n\\nChase polished her general management skills at Harvard Business School and holds an undergraduate degree from the University of the South.\\n\\nWhen she\\u2019s not working with clients, Chase can be found serving on the Board of Directors for the Alliance for Education, planning her next Seafair party, hiking and practicing yoga, or brushing up on her Spanish for another trip to Mexico.\",\"83\":\"chase.morgan@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Chase-Morgan-v2.jpg\",\"86\":\"Help! Why Aren\\u2019t We Winning in the Cloud?\",\"82\":\"Partner\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '379f9e3f-12e1-4034-b14d-3ce93d90340d'),
 ('287', '578', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Rebecca Jones\",\"slug\":\"rebecca-jones\",\"postDate\":1471304271,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Rebecca is a business manager and Partner who\\u00a0knows how to reach and engage customers. She has two decades of experience working with organizations like AT&T Wireless, T-Mobile, Microsoft, and Seattle Children\\u2019s Hospital. \\u00a0 She partners with leadership in marketing and sales to define campaign and go-to-market strategy, build repeatable frameworks, and implement results-driven marketing programs.\\n\\u00a0\\nRebecca has led teams on the agency and company side and has deep industry expertise in technology and mobile. Rebecca is passionate about the art of developing meaningful customer stories, driving results through a lean-process approach to marketing, and helping clients transform their marketing organizations and deliver sustainable growth through digital and marketing automation. \\u00a0\\n\\u00a0\\nRebecca resides in Seattle, Washington and holds a BA\\u00a0in Fine Arts and English Literature from Lake Forest College. \\u00a0When she\'s not at work, Rebecca spends time with family and friends, chasing adventure with her husband and two sons, and enjoying the perfect glass of wine.\",\"83\":\"rebecca.jones@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Rebecca-Jones.jpg\",\"86\":\"How Marketing Leaders are Moving to the CloudFraming a Conversation\",\"82\":\"Partner\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', '2016-08-15 23:37:51', 'd776da12-72da-4546-9ca5-3ee5e3268cad'),
 ('288', '579', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Patty Vu\",\"slug\":\"patty-vu\",\"postDate\":1471304271,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"Patty brings to the table solid experience in process optimization and execution plus developing skills in marketing and project management. She is recognized for her critical thinking and attention to detail, as well as for keeping even keel, full steam ahead under tight deadlines and high pressure. Patty thrives on stepping into a project with multiple work streams, dependencies, stakeholders, and cross-functional teams to optimize work and collaboration.\\n\\nPatty holds a double degree in business administration and economics from the University of Washington, with concentrations in marketing and finance.\\n\\nIn her free time, she enjoys the company of her family and friends. Animal rescue also ranks high on her list.\",\"83\":\"patty.vu@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/Patty-Vu.jpg\",\"86\":\"\",\"82\":\"Senior Consultant\",\"87\":\"Consultant\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:52', '2016-08-15 23:37:52', '64563f59-cc08-4af8-9a79-2a1322aeefd7'),
 ('289', '580', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"John Tribble\",\"slug\":\"john-tribble\",\"postDate\":1471304272,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"84\":\"John loves analytical projects such as ROI modeling and problem solving. He excels in bringing consensus across multiple groups, especially in situations that require diplomacy. He is energized by the treasure hunt aspect of consulting. John strives to blaze new trails and to learn or achieve something new. Reaching goals and exceeding clients\\u2019 expectations fuel John\\u2019s engine.\\n\\nKnown for his creativity, John is adept at identifying time and resource efficiencies to make teams more effective. He\\u2019s even brought lessons learned coaching youth sports into business team settings.\\n\\nJohn\\u2019s into soccer, golf, and triathlons. His kids make him laugh on a daily basis.\",\"83\":\"john.tribble@bridgepartnersconsulting.com\",\"85\":\"\\/images\\/uploads\\/people\\/John-Tribble-2.jpg\",\"86\":\"Perspectives from the Pitch: Building Strong TeamsFour Coaching Pitfalls to AvoidHow to Tell Your Boss He is Wrong\",\"82\":\"Director\",\"87\":\"Leadership\"}}', '2016-08-15 23:37:52', '2016-08-15 23:37:52', 'ac775c3d-e370-4503-ba6e-a6aaa81a0cdd');
